        <h2 style="margin-top: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">Adding
            New Gadgets</font></h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><strong><font color="#000000">Gadgets</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> can be added either to shelves or to the desktop
            itself. In order to add </font><strong><font color="#000000">Gadgets</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> to the desktop, go to </font><em><font color="#000000">Main
              Menu -&gt; Settings -&gt; Gadgets</font></em><font color="#000000">
            and the </font><strong><font color="#000000">Desktop Gadgets</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> dialog will open. </font> </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm" align="center"><font color="#000000"><img
              src="../images/Desktop-gadgets.jpg" name="Image5" border="0" width="75"
              height="38" align="bottom"> </font> </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">Select a </font><strong><font
              color="#000000">Gadget</font></strong><font color="#000000"> in
            the list, and press </font><em><font color="#000000">Add Gadget</font></em><font
            color="#000000">. The </font><strong><font color="#000000">Gadget</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> appears at the top left of the desktop with a blue
            crosshatching, indicating it can be moved and resized to your
            requirements. When the </font><strong><font color="#000000">Gadget</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> is in the proper place, </font><em><font color="#000000">right-click</font></em><font
            color="#000000"> the </font><strong><font color="#000000">Gadget</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> to lock it. </font> </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm" align="center"><font color="#000000"><img
              src="../images/gadget-manager.png" name="Image6" border="0" width="75"
              height="38" align="bottom"> </font> </p>
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">Adding
            a Gadget to a Shelf</font></h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">Adding a </font><strong><font
              color="#000000">Gadget</font></strong><font color="#000000"> to a
          </font><strong><font color="#000000">Shelf</font></strong><font color="#000000">
            requires a slightly different procedure. See the <a href="shelves.html">Shelves
              Section</a> of this Guide for details. </font> </p>
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">Gadget
            Settings</font></h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">Once they are
            placed on the desktop or on a </font><strong><font color="#000000">Shelf</font></strong><font
            color="#000000">, each </font><strong><font color="#000000">Gadget</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> can be right-clicked to configure its appearance
            and its behavior. For example, when you first install the </font><em><font
              color="#000000">Forecasts</font></em><font color="#000000"> </font><strong><font
              color="#000000">Gadget</font></strong><font color="#000000">, it
            gives you the weather for Sofia, Bulgaria. That is probably not what
            you want (unless, of course, you live there). So right-click it,
            open the menu </font><em><font color="#000000">Gadget Forecasts
              -&gt; Forecasts Settings</font></em><font color="#000000">. In the
            dialog box that appears, you will see instructions for finding and
            entering the code for your city. </font> </p>
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">Gadgets
            Need Their Modules</font></h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">What </font><strong><font
              color="#000000">Gadgets</font></strong><font color="#000000"> you
            have available to add is determined by what </font><strong><font color="#000000">Modules</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> you have </font><em><font color="#000000">Loaded</font></em><font
            color="#000000">. </font><em><font color="#000000">Loading</font></em><font
            color="#000000"> a </font><strong><font color="#000000">Module</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> reads it from disk storage and places it in RAM,
            but it won't be displayed on screen until you add it as a </font><strong><font
              color="#000000">Gadget</font></strong><font color="#000000"> to
            the desktop or a </font><strong><font color="#000000">Shelf</font></strong><font
            color="#000000">. To </font><em><font color="#000000">Load/Unload</font></em><font
            color="#000000"> </font><strong><font color="#000000">Modules</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> go to </font><em><font color="#000000">Main Menu
              -&gt; Settings -&gt; Modules</font></em><font color="#000000">.
            See the <a href="modules.html">Modules Section</a> of this Guide
            for more details. </font> </p>
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">Still
            more Gadgets</font></h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">To keep the
            initial download and installation of </font><strong><font color="#000000">Bodhi
              Linux</font></strong><font color="#000000"> as compact as
            possible, some excellent </font><strong><font color="#000000">Modules</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> were not included, but can be downloaded and
            installed via the </font><strong><font color="#000000">Synaptic
              Package Manager</font></strong><font color="#000000"> just like
            other Linux programs. </font> </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">For a full list
            of available </font><strong><font color="#000000">Gadgets</font></strong><font
            color="#000000"> check the <a href="module_reference.html">Module
              Reference</a>. </font> </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0.53cm"><font color="#000000">See the <a href="modules.html">Modules
              Section</a> of this Guide for more details. </font> </p>
